HEADWORD: Hollow-hearted
<hw>Hol"low-heart`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Insincere;
deceitful; not sound and true; having a cavity or decayed spot
within.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Faithless; dishonest; false;
treacherous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hollow-horned</ent>⟦br⟧
